{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17654878","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17654878"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:56:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:56:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18639"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18639","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18639"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.69,0.09,0,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11371"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78382"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11371","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11371"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18639"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63744"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6801"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26384"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26685"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78382","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78382"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe lower trachea has important anatomical relationships with surrounding structures in the superior mediastinum.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the anatomical position of the lower trachea?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Between the left and right main bronchi","Anterior to the oesophagus and posterior to the aortic arch","Anterior to the aortic arch","Lateral to the azygos vein","Posterior to the oesophagus"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe lower trachea is positioned \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior to the oesophagus and posterior to the aortic arch\u003C/strong\u003E in the superior mediastinum. This relationship is clinically significant as compression from surrounding structures can affect the airway.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBetween the left and right main bronchi\u003C/strong\u003E - The trachea is superior to the bronchi, bifurcating into them at the carina\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnterior to the aortic arch\u003C/strong\u003E - The aortic arch crosses anterior to the trachea\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELateral to the azygos vein\u003C/strong\u003E - The azygos vein arches over the right main bronchus, not the trachea\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPosterior to the oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E - The trachea lies anterior to the oesophagus throughout its course\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe trachea bifurcates at the level of thoracic vertebra T4-T5 into the right and left main bronchi. The right main bronchus is wider, shorter and more vertical than the left main bronchus.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The lower trachea is located anterior to the oesophagus and posterior to the aortic arch at the level of thoracic vertebra T4.","The trachea bifurcates into right and left main bronchi at the carina, typically at the level of thoracic vertebra T4-T5.","The azygos vein arches over the right main bronchus to join the superior vena cava."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63744"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18639"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63744","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63744"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T14:23:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T14:24:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11371"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78382"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4927","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4927"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:14:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50:22+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"13"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4